      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: emit warning on consecutive QueuedFileWriter failures",
        "body": "> [!NOTE]\n> This PR is AI-assisted (authored with OpenClaw/MillieClaw agent tooling).\n\n## Problem\n\n`QueuedFileWriter` catches all write errors with `.catch(() => undefined)` and continues silently. When the disk fills up, all payload log and audit trail writes fail with no indication — the queue keeps processing but producing no output. Operators have no signal that diagnostic data is being lost.\n\nCloses #57031\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe `.catch(() => undefined)` handler in the write chain swallows all errors unconditionally. There is no failure counter, no warning, and no backpressure signal.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Track `consecutiveFailures` count per writer instance\n- Reset to 0 on successful write\n- Emit a `console.warn` on every failure at or past the threshold of 3 consecutive failures (includes file path and error message)\n- Add `drain()` method to `QueuedFileWriter` for deterministic queue completion\n\n## Testing\n\n- Added `queued-file-writer.test.ts` with 5 tests:\n  - Writes lines to file correctly (using `drain()`)\n  - Reuses existing writer for same path\n  - Emits warning after 3 consecutive failures\n  - Warning fires on every failure at or past threshold (not just once)\n  - Resets failure count on successful write (2 fails → success → 2 more fails → no warning)\n- Updated existing test mocks in `anthropic-payload-log.test.ts` and `cache-trace.test.ts` to include `drain()`\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-57031",
